-- Regression for GH issue #55: a Markdown blockquote inside a doc comment
-- ("-- > prose, not an expression") extracts as a doctest "input line" the
-- same as a real example ("-- > expr"), and the synthesized snippet fails to
-- parse.  Before the fix, `buildSynthDecls` ran every example's `parse`
-- through the compiler's PANICKING entry and concatenated the results before
-- running any of them, so ONE malformed example uncatchably aborted the
-- WHOLE file's doctest run — a file with real, valid doctests reported none
-- of them.  The fix routes each example through the non-panicking
-- `parseResult` entry individually: a malformed example becomes a single
-- located `ERROR`, and every OTHER example in the file still runs.
--
-- > inc 1
-- 2
--
-- Note:
--
-- > This is prose in a Markdown blockquote, not a doctest.
--
-- > inc 4
-- 5
export inc : Int -> Int
inc n = n + 1
